	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">blargg wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">On all my old-style SNES consoles, the RF modulator is built in, with an RCA connector on the back that outputs it (just like the NES). The modulator is a separate metal-shielded module inside the NES/SNES The external gray box is just an automatic RF switch.</div><br />On top of that, there is in fact a difference regarding the built-in RF modulator. On US and PAL consoles, the small switch allows you to select between channels 3 and 4. On Japanese Super Famicoms, you switch between channels 1 and 2. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" />

		

		</td>
	</tr>
